## Citations

- California Government Code §65080 — Regional Transportation Plan scoring frameworks and update cycles.
- California Public Resources Code §21099 + CEQA Guidelines §15064.3 — transportation-impact VMT significance (threshold overrides referenced here flow to the new run's manifest for Planner Pack CEQA reruns).
- Governor's Office of Planning and Research, *Technical Advisory on Evaluating Transportation Impacts in CEQA* (December 2018) — 15% default threshold below regional/citywide reference VMT per capita.
- California Streets & Highways Code §§2380–2383 — Active Transportation Program weighting criteria (ATP weights 30/25/25/20 → safety/equity/climate/feasibility mirror the ClawModeler default).

## Notes

- This report is a **screening-level** record of a parameter override.
  It does not constitute a formal CEQA finding, RTP amendment, or ATP
  resubmission.
- Planner Pack artifacts (CEQA, LAPM, RTP, equity, ATP) are **not**
  automatically re-generated for the new run. Run
  `clawmodeler-engine planner-pack <module> --run-id {{ result.new_run_id }}`
  for any Planner Pack deliverable you need on this scenario.
- The manifest at `runs/{{ result.new_run_id }}/manifest.json` records
  the applied overrides and `base_run_id` so downstream diff + QA
  workflows can trace provenance.

